<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
Throughout Europe, to Western Asia and North Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Arndt, E." journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" title="Ground Beetles (Carabidae) of Greece." year="2011">Arndt et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
In agricultural areas, it is often found on arable land, pastureland and alfalfa. It is usually absent in fields with abundant weed cover (
<bibRefCitation author="Holland, J" journalOrPublisher="Integrated Pest Management Reviews" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" pagination="109 - 129" title="The Effects of Agricultural Practices on Carabidae in Temperate Agroecosystems." volume="5" year="2000">Holland and Luff 2000</bibRefCitation>
). It likes open areas and is an autumn breeder (
<bibRefCitation author="Thiele, H." journalOrPublisher="Springer, Berlin / Heidelberg" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" title="Carabid Beetles in Their Environments" year="1977">Thiele 1977</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, it was found in the maize field in the homogeneous area (n = 1), the olive grove in the homogeneous area (n = 3) and the wheat field in the homogeneous area (n = 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
